com.simukappu.coherence.distributed.fifo

Interface FifoDistributedBiFunction<T,R>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The function argument class and the key class of coherence cache for FIFO distributed processing
    R - The function return class
    All Superinterfaces:
    BiFunction<T,String,R>, FifoDistributedBiProcessor<T>
    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface FifoDistributedBiFunction<T,R>
extends FifoDistributedBiProcessor<T>, BiFunction<T,String,R>
    FunctionalInterface extends BiFunction to distributed processing as First in, first out.
    This function calls putIfAbsent-like method to coherence cache with a key and then call process method only when the entry is first in.
    We have to call this interface with a stream including coherence cache name to use as the key set for distributed processing
    Author:
    Shota Yamazaki
